<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Espy" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Espy,</orth> 1) to perceive, to see, to discover: <bibl n="shak. ven 261" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 261</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 361" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 361</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 5" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.262" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 262</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.105" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.97" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 2, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.194" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 194</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> Double accus.: <cit><quote>he doth e. himself love's traitor,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.506" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 506</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to watch, to observe: <cit><quote>we are --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 48</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>